Section 1:
132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 923
H.P. 588 House of Representatives, March 11, 2025
Maine by Removing Requirements for Supplemental Guide Signs on
the Interstate Highway System
Received by the Clerk of the House on March 5, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Transportation pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed pursuant to Joint Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative FRIEDMANN of Bar Harbor.
Cosponsored by Senator GROHOSKI of Hancock.
Printed on recycled paper
1 Be it enacted by the People of the State of Maine as follows:
2 Sec. 1. 23 MRSA §1912-C, sub-§5, ¶A, as enacted by PL 2013, c. 549, §3, is
3 amended to read:
4 A. A college or university that:;
5 (1) Is located within 15 miles of an exit and has an enrollment of 300 or more
6 students attending classes on site; or
7 (2) Has an enrollment of 1,000 or more students attending classes on site;
8 SUMMARY
99 This bill removes the location and enrollment requirements that a college or university
1100 must meet to appear on a supplemental guide sign on the interstate highway system.
Page 1 - 132LR1806(01)
